05080nam a22008175i 9783110909623DE-B159720211217065530.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211217t20112004gw     fo  d z      eng d  a97831109096237 a10.1515/97831109096232doi  a(DE-B1597)56341  a(OCoLC)979640726  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 4aP325.5.M36 7aLAN0090002bisacsh04a401.3a414.6  aET 4802rvk0(DE-625)rvk/27992:1 aSchalley, Andrea C., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aCognitive Modeling and Verbal Semantics :bA Representational Framework Based on UML /cAndrea C. Schalley. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter Mouton, c[2011] 4c©2004  a1 online resource (446 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aTrends in Linguistics. Studies and Monographs [TiLSM] ,x1861-4302 ;v1540 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis book presents a unique approach to the semantics of verbs. It develops and specifies a decompositional representation framework for verbal semantics that is based on the Unified Modeling Language (UML), the graphical lingua franca for the design and modeling of object-oriented systems in computer science. The new framework combines formal precision with conceptual flexibility and allows the representation of very complicated details of verbal meaning, using a mixture of graphical elements as well as linearized constructs. Thereby, it offers a solution for different semantic problems such as context-dependency and polysemy. The latter, for instance, is demonstrated in one of the two well-elaborated applications of the framework within this book, the investigation of the polysemy of German setzen. Besides the formal specification of the framework, the book comprises a cognitive interpretation of important modeling elements, discusses general issues connected with the framework such as dynamic and static aspects of verbal meanings, questions of granularity, and general constraints applying to verbal semantics. Moreover, first steps towards a compositional semantics are undertaken, and a new verb classification based on this graphical approach is proposed. Since the framework is graphical in nature, the book contains many annotated figures, and the framework's modeling elements are illustrated by example diagrams. Not only scholars working in the field of linguistics, in particular in semantics, will find this book illuminating because of its new graphical approach, but also researchers of cognitive science, computational linguistics and computer science in general will surely appreciate it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aCognitive grammar. 0aProgramming languages (Electronic computers)xSemantics. 0aSemanticsxMathematical models. 0aUML (Computer science). 4aInformatik. 4aKognitionswissenschaft. 4aSemantik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Linguistics and Semiotics  2000-2014 (EN)z978311023845708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Backlist 2000-2015z97831107429610 cprintz978311017951440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311090962340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110909623423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110909623/original  a978-3-11-023845-7  DGBA Backlist Linguistics and Semiotics  2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  a978-3-11-074296-1  De Gruyter M